@%META:TOPICINFO{author="EelcoVisser" date="1073225215" format="1.0" version="1.3"}%
%META:TOPICPARENT{name="HotSpots"}%
Some notes about being a program chair of [[http://www.program-transformation.org/GPCE][GPCE'04]], so that I remember it the next time. 

Website

	* a wiki is great for maintaining a conference website since everyone can edit

Schedule; include time for

	* paper selection, reviewing, PC meeting, paper revision, preparing proceedings, printing

Picking a program committee

	* coverage, experts, rotation

Reviewing process

	* "[[http://www.iam.unibe.ch/~oscar/Champion/champion.html][Identify the Champion]]'' An Organisational Pattern Language for Programme Committees by [[http://www.iam.unibe.ch/~oscar/][Oscar Nierstrasz]]
	* [[http://www.acm.org/sigplan/oopsla/oopsla96/how93.html][How to Get a Paper Accepted at OOPSLA]]

Submission and reviewing software

	* [[http://www.cyberchair.org][CyberChair]]
	* [[http://www.logic.at/staff/salzer/confpack/][Conference Management Software]]
	* [[http://www.acm.org/sigs/sgb/summary.html][a survey of conference management software by the ACM]]

@


